{In this structure, White has sacrificed the b2-pawn, but the queens are on
the board. In such positions, Black should be careful as the king is not that
safe in the center anymore. In order to protect his king, Black usually
castles long. I think that with a careful play, Black holds the balance in
such structures.}  *

