1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Rg1 e5 7. Nb3 Be6 8. g4
d5 9. exd5 (9. g5 {is another way to reach the endgame, but knowing that one
of Black's ideas is to provoke this advance in the endgame, I would say that
this is even a slightly improved version for him} Nxe4 10. Nxe4 dxe4 11. Qxd8+
Kxd8 12. Bg2 Kc7 13. Bxe4 Nc6 $11) 9... Nxd5 10. Nxd5 Qxd5 11. Be3 Nc6 12. Qxd5
Bxd5 13. O-O-O O-O-O 14. g5 $6 {This advance is dubious from a strategical
point of view. It seems to gain space on the kingside, but actually Black will
use the pawn as a hook to open the h-file.} (14. Bb6 {or}) (14. Be2 {should be
more reliable}) 14... Kc7 $1 {Preventing Bb6.} 15. Bh3 $6 {This will bring
White problems.} (15. Be2 g6 16. h4 h6 17. a3 {seems still equal} hxg5 18. hxg5
Rh4 19. Rd2 Be6 20. Rxd8 Nxd8 21. Nc5 Bf5 22. c3 $11) (15. a4 {[%cal Ya4a5]
was also playable} Be6 16. Rxd8 Nxd8 17. a5 Nc6 18. Bb6+ Kc8 19. Nd2 {[%cal
Yd2c4]}) 15... g6 $1 {[%cal Gh7h6] h6 in the next move is already unpleasant.}
({White was probably just counting on} 15... h6 16. g6 $1 {when Black has no
advantage}) 16. f4 $2 ({White could still avoid the worst with} 16. Bg4 h6 17.
h4 {after} hxg5 18. hxg5 Rh4 {I think Black is a bit more active, but White
has no serious problems and should keep the balance}) 16... h6 $1 17. fxe5 hxg5
18. Bxg5 Bh6 $1 {Maybe the move missed by White.} 19. Bxh6 Rxh6 20. Bg2 $8 Bxg2
21. Rxd8 Kxd8 22. Rxg2 Nxe5 $17 {[%csl Gf7,Rh2] The endgame is much better for
Black - he has a passed pawn already, pressure on h2 and more active pieces.}
23. Nc5 Kc7 24. Nd3 $6 (24. Re2 f6 25. c3 a5 26. b3 b6 27. Ne4 Ng4 28. Kd2 f5
29. Nf2 Rxh2 $1 {Black wins the pawn endgame.} 30. Nxg4 Rxe2+ 31. Kxe2 fxg4 32.
Ke3 Kc6 33. Kf4 Kd5 $19) 24... Nxd3+ $1 {White was betting on drawing chances
of rook endgames, but Black knows what he is doing, as his king and rook will
be more active than the opponent's.} 25. cxd3 Kd6 26. Kd2 f5 27. Ke3 Ke5 28.
d4+ Kf6 29. d5 $5 {White looks for desperate measures to activate his pieces,
or at least one of them.} (29. Kd3 b5 $1 30. Kc3 a5 $1 {[%csl Gc3] The king
can't be activated}) (29. Rd2 $2 Rh3+ $19) (29. Kd2 f4 30. Kd3 Kf5 31. d5 g5
$19 {is an easy win for Black}) 29... Ke5 30. d6 Kxd6 31. Kf4 Ke6 32. Kg5 Rh8
$1 {This resource secures Black's advantage.} 33. Rc2 (33. Kxg6 $2 Rg8+ $19)
33... Rf8 $1 {[%cal Gf5f1] By supporting the f-pawn now, Black wins.} 34. Re2+
(34. h4 $5 {was White's best chance} Rh8 $1 35. Rc4 $8 (35. Re2+ Kf7 $19 {
[%cal Yh8h5]}) 35... Rd8 $1 36. Rb4 (36. Kxg6 Rg8+ 37. Kh7 (37. Kh5 Kf6 {
[%cal Gg8h8]}) 37... Rg4 $1 $19) 36... b5 37. a4 Rd2 38. axb5 Rg2+ 39. Kh6 axb5
40. Rxb5 f4 $19) 34... Kd5 35. Kxg6 f4 $19 {The f-pawn is unstoppable now.} 36.
Kg7 Rf5 37. Kg6 f3 $1 38. Rf2 Ke4 39. h4 Rf8 40. Kg7 Rc8 41. h5 Ke3 0-1

