1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bc4 e6 7. Bb3 b5 8. O-O
Be7 9. Qf3 {The main line for White after 6.Bc4. Instead of early pawn
advances in the center, White opts for quick development of pieces, winning
some tempos. Right now the threat is e5, and the queen will later find an
ideal square on g3.} Qc7 (9... Bb7 $2 {would be bad in view of the already
familiar} 10. Bxe6 $1) 10. Qg3 (10. e5 $2 Bb7 11. exd6 Bxd6 {just gives Black
an active position for nothing.}) 10... O-O 11. Bh6 $1 {Natural and good.
White develops the bishop with tempo and disturbs Black's development.} Ne8 12.
Rad1 {This seems the most natural, keeping the other rook flexible, as White
can play Rfe1 or support f4-f5 in the next moves.} (12. Rfe1 {was played a few
times} Bf6 $1 {Black improves the bishop, wins a tempo and also sets a subtle
trap.} 13. Be3 (13. Rad1 {is natural, developing and bad:} Be5 14. Qg4 Bxd4 $1
15. Rxd4 e5 $19 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Gc8g4] ;Gdanski,J (2505)-Kempinski,R (2385)
POL-ch 51th Gdansk 1994 (8) 0-1}) (13. Nf3 {also didn't pose Black any
problems.} Nc6 14. Rad1 Bb7 15. Bf4 Rd8 16. h4 Kh8 17. Rd3 Ne5 $1 18. Bxe5 dxe5
19. Rxd8 Qxd8 {This change of structure is generally better for Black, as his
pawns restrict the opponent's minor pieces very effectively. It may seem that
Black has problems regarding his development, but as Giri shows, this is not
really an issue.} 20. Rd1 Qc7 21. a3 g6 22. Ng5 Bc8 $1 {[%csl Ye6] Good
prophylaxis on e6.} 23. Qd3 Be7 24. Qe2 Nf6 25. Rd3 h6 26. Nf3 Kg7 $17 {
[%cal Ge7c5] Black kept improving his pieces in a very instructive way -
Tissir,M (2388)-Giri,A (2755) Baku ol (Men) 42nd 2016 (1.1) 0-1.}) 13... Bd7 {
Black follows the normal development scheme from the main lines, which seems
sufficient to get a good position.} 14. a3 Nc6 15. Nxc6 Bxc6 16. Bf4 a5 $1 17.
Qd3 Qb7 $15 {[%cal Gb5b4,Ga5a4,Ya8d8,Ye8c7] Black is fine. Apart from the pawn
advances always available on the queenside, he has no problems finishing his
development with Rd8 and Nc7 - Sevian, S (2371)-Troff, K (2421) USA-ch Saint
Louis 2013 (5) 0-1.}) ({Some years ago I faced} 12. Be3 $5 {, which is, in fact,
