Rc7a5]}) 14... Nc5 15. e5 (15. Nd2 e5 $1 {is bad for White} 16. Nf5 g6) 15...
dxe5 16. fxe5 Nd5 17. Bxe7 Nxe7 18. Nd2 Bb7 19. Nc4 O-O $17 {Black has an
obvious advantage, as his king is out of any danger, while he has the better
structure and good play on the queenside.} *

