instead of repeating moves, White's idea should be} 17. c4 {[%cal Yb1c3] to
win some space. Still, after} Nc5 18. Nc3 Nxb3 19. axb3 Qb4 {[%cal Yc8d7]
Black's position looks very solid}) 16... b5 $1 {the right move to avoid
White's plan of Nb1 and c4} 17. Qe3 ({this used to be considered risky because
of} 17. Bxb5 $2 axb5 18. Nxb5 Qa4 19. Nc7+ Kf8 20. Nxa8 Qxa8 $19 {but it is
easy to see that Black is winning here}) 17... Bb7 18. f5 $2 (18. Nb1 $5 Qxa2
19. N1d2 Bd8 $1 $13 {[%cal Gd8b6]}) 18... Ne5 {[%csl Ge5] whenever White
rushes to advance f5, Black obtains a solid post for his knight in the center}
19. Qb6 $2 (19. Nb1 $142 Qa4 20. Nc3 $11) 19... Bc6 20. fxe6 fxe6 21. Bg4 Bd7
$19 {[%cal Ya8c8,Ga3b4] ;Pruijssers,R (2261)-Senff,M (2467) Dieren op 2005 (2)
