30. Qf5+ $11) 27. Qxd7+ Nxd7 28. gxh4 Rc8 $15 {again with a better endgame for
Black}) 16... e4 $1 {An important move, trying to discoordinate White's forces.
} 17. Bh5+ (17. Qc4 {Geske,J (2402)-Maksimenko,A (2547) AUT-chT 1314 2013 (6.2)
1/2-1/2} Nd7 $1 18. Nxe4 (18. Rxb7 Nc5 19. Bh5+ Kf8 20. Rb1 Rg8 $1 21. O-O Rg5
