10... Qxb2 $2 11. Nb3 {[%cal Ga1a2] and Black is in trouble}) (10... Nc6 $5) (
10... Nbd7 {was MVL's move, but after} 11. O-O-O {Black felt uncomfortable
enough to play} g5 $6 12. fxg5 Ne5 13. Qd2 Nh7 {[%csl Gh7] the knight stands
poorly on h7} 14. Nf3 hxg5 15. Bf2 Qc7 16. Be2 Bd7 17. h4 $36 {with a great
position for White, although MVL showed great defensive skills to survive -
Caruana,F (2807) -Vachier Lagrave,M (2791) Sinquefield Cup 5th 2017 (6) 1/2-1/2
}) 11. Bxe7 {Black has two options now, the safest being} Nxc3 ({and the
double-edged} 11... Qxb2 $5 {going for a long and forced line} 12. Nxe4 Qxa1+
13. Kf2 Kxe7 14. Nf5+ $1 exf5 15. Qxd6+ Ke8 16. Bb5+ $1 {White keeps
sacrificing his pieces to win the queen} axb5 17. Rxa1 fxe4 {a difficult
position to evaluate, Black has sufficient material for the queen, but it
