its counterpart, which would be very useful for attacking purposes on the
kingside.} 16. Nh4 (16. Bd2 Bd4 $1 {[%cal Yd7c5] with counterplay in center
for Black} 17. Nh4 Nc5 18. Rd1 Nxd3 19. cxd3 Bc8 $1 {[%csl Gf5] and the bishop
is replaced at the right moment to protect the important f5-square}) 16... g6
$1 {Black is able to stop the knight from coming to f5.} 17. Bxc5 (17. Bxh6 Ng4
18. Bd2 Bf2 $1 19. Rxf2 Qxh4 {[%csl Yf2,Yh2] is the tactical reason behind 16..
.g6!}) 17... Nxc5 18. Qf2 Nxd3 19. cxd3 Re6 20. Rad1 Qe7 {[%csl Gd3][%cal
Ya8d8,Ye6d6] And Black is at least ok.} *

